Dry
1 cup whole wheat flour
1/2 cup buckwheet flour
2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp baking powder
1 tsp sugar
1/4ish tsp Salt

Wet
1 tsp vanilla extract
1 egg
1 - 1/2 cups milk
1/4 cup olive oil
1 cup plain yogurt (any kind)

1. Mix dry ingredients
2. Add all wet ingredients except yogurt
  * NOTE: may need more or less milk.  You want a runniness slightly more runny than normal pancakes as the whole wheat bran will absorb some liquid during step 4.
3. Mix well.
4. Let rest in refridgerator a minimum of 15 minutes
5. Add yogurt and mix well.
6. Let sit 5 minutes
7. Cook!
